    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1054</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d367fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis,</hi> on the same date, to the Ambassador in France (No.
                        3154).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-07T22:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1918, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6491. Embassy Petrograd reports that <persName>Kamenev</persName> has been
                    appointed Envoy Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary at Large of the <pb
                        facs="0444" n="370" xml:id="pg_370"/> Bolshevik government and
                        <persName>Zalkind</persName> appointed in the same capacity to Switzerland
                    and that passports of both have been visaed by British representatives. Please
                    ascertain if report regarding visa is true.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
